Text Count: 3266, reading time approximately 5.5 minutes

Introduction: This simple question, which was originally written in the institutional settings program, has become the soul of hundreds of thousands of Chinese disease controllers.

By Ma Xiaohua

What can our disease control and prevention departments do in the face of a public health emergency? But how?

By Ma Xiaohua

What can our disease control and prevention departments do in the face of a public health emergency? But how?

The simple question, which had been written in the agency's programming, became the soul of hundreds of thousands of Chinese disease controllers. More awkwardly, this torture, which was proposed during the SARS outbreak in 2003, remains unanswered 17 years later as the new pneumonia epidemic rages.

After the outbreak of this epidemic, someone dug up last year during the national two sessions, "there will be no more SARS, " Takatomi, director of the The National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, told a crowd of reporters. Because our country's infectious disease prevention and control system has been well established, we can stop the virus when it comes, the Punch in the face came so fast.

From December 12,2019, when the first case of NCP was received, to 2400 hours on February 22,2019, a total of 76,936 confirmed cases and 2,442 cumulative deaths were reported from the National Health Commission website.

We can not deny the efforts and achievements made by the Department of Disease Control and Prevention, but there are many shortcomings in this epidemic from early warning to prevention and control, which is also an indisputable fact. In an interview with China Business News, Yang Gonghuan, the former deputy director of the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention, even argued that the functional positioning of "China Disease Control" is unclear, and that it is facing difficulties such as lack of talents, these make it difficult to play its due role in dealing with public health emergencies.

So how did this embarrassment come about? How do we crack it?

A big cat with no teeth?

As early as 1982, the then Ministry of Health decided to establish the China Preventive Medicine Center, which was renamed the Chinese Academy of Preventive Medicine in 1983. The establishment of the China Preventive Medicine Center marks the establishment of a National Preventive Medicine Center, a provincial, prefectural and county-level health and epidemic prevention station, a township health center, a street hospital, a village clinic, and various specialized prevention and treatment stations at various levels, national Disease Prevention and Control System.

On January 23,2002, the Chinese Academy of Preventive Medicine officially changed its name to the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention. The China Center for Health Supervision was also established. This means that China's new disease prevention and control system is gradually taking shape. China's public health system at this time was composed of medical administrative departments at various levels, hospitals, disease prevention and control institutions, health supervision institutions and so on.

The next year saw the outbreak of SARS in 2003, which led to the construction of China's Emerging Infectious Diseases, and the emphasis on the disease control system. At that time, the requirement of establishing and perfecting the disease prevention and Control System within 3 years was put forward. The financial input of CDC at all levels increased rapidly, and the hardware condition of CDC improved greatly.

By the end of 2004, there were 3,586 Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (cdcs) in various parts of the country, with a total staff of about 210,000, including the preventive health centers. Over the next 10 years, there were no substantial changes in the staffing of the CDC.

Even with roughly the same number of temporary workers, Yang thinks the number of people per 10,000 in China's disease-control departments is low. At the same time, disease control departments at all levels there is a shortage of professional talent, the proportion of versatile talent is insufficient "false saturation" phenomenon.

However, many local centers for Disease Control and Prevention and health supervision institutions are faced with confusion over the treatment of their personnel, the nature of their institutions and the prospects for development. The loss of key personnel has become increasingly acute. Some County Centers for Disease Control and Prevention have not hired professional staff for more than 10 years, the CDC team is in danger of being hollowed out.

In this situation, the four-level National Health and epidemic prevention system is becoming increasingly fragile, and the original three-level primary health care and preventive health care network is gradually being dismantled. The phenomenon of "emphasizing medical treatment over prevention, emphasizing paid over unpaid, emphasizing more benefits over less benefits" is prominent, the weakness of the disease prevention system has a tendency to regress to pre-SARS levels.

It is also worth mentioning that the CDC is in fact a big cat without teeth, it is in the event of a public health emergency, it is not directly to issue an outbreak notification. Why? Yang Gonghuan explained that because China's Disease Control Agency is not an administrative department, but a public institution, it does not have the authority to release information about the outbreak.

On April 22 last year, when the 13th session of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress considered the report on the management of the medical profession and the implementation of the law on practicing physicians in sub groups, Vice Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress Chen Zhu proposed that, we should attach great importance to the risk of weakening the functions of the disease prevention and control system in the reform of public institutions, and make clear the functions of CDC at all levels as soon as possible.

The debate on reform

Although prevention has always been the guiding principle of health and health work in our country since the founding ceremony of the People's Republic of China, the tendency of emphasizing medical treatment over public health has not been corrected for a long time.

The above-mentioned report reviewed by the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress points out that since the new round of institutional reform in 2018, some provinces have optimized the integration of various public institutions, including the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, most of the prefectural-level cities and all county-level CDC in individual provinces have implemented a model of integration with other public institutions, with some under the leadership of the National Health Commission and others under the direct leadership of the government, breaking the chain of the old top-down CDC system. In addition, after the abolition of administrative fees, some local governments have not yet established a long-term and stable investment guarantee mechanism for Disease Control and Prevention, and the salaries of the staff of disease control and prevention institutions are obviously lower than those of public hospitals at the same level, leading to a serious brain drain.

Before the bottom of the "three-level health care network" is basically no longer exist, replaced by the "three-level health services network" , played down its preventive health care function. Some in the industry believe that this approach is very questionable.

These reforms were, in fact, largely proposed by health-care experts, "none of whom could spell out the disease. ". Yang Gonghuan thinks, put public health, disease control, medical treatment to wait together, natural chaos. In particular, the prevention and control of infectious diseases, and chronic disease prevention and control, occupational health, nutritional health, are not quite the same, can not be put together.

In today's world of Emerging Infectious Diseases and known infectious disease outbreaks without Borders, timely detection, early warning and early action are the major tasks and challenges of Disease Prevention and control at this stage. Having experienced the painful lessons of SARS, China has stepped up the construction of its infectious disease prevention and Control System, making major infectious disease prevention and control one of the 16 major scientific and technological projects since the 11th five-year plan, it is also included in the national programme for medium-and long-term scientific and technological development. The Zhejiang University has built a state key laboratory for the diagnosis and treatment of infectious diseases. However, in fact, the prevention and control of infectious diseases, or the work of public health together.

Yang Gonghuan suggested that the prevention and control of infectious diseases should be separated from the prevention and control of chronic diseases and the prevention and control of Dawei health. There should be a core team for the prevention and control of infectious diseases, as well as a network with hospitals, community health service centers, research institutes and universities. Because the study of the Etiology of infectious diseases, detection methods, including some in-depth research models of epidemiology, need to have basic research support and information support. But once the infectious disease epidemic situation occurs, it will also involve the medical resources deployment, the material mobilization, the logistic support and so on. So, it needs to be put into the administration, it needs to be an administration.

"It doesn't make sense to separate the work of the professionals and the administration of the government. If you look at other countries, there is no such binary approach. The CDC is only at the national level, and below the state level it is the health bureau, and all the disease control tasks are done by the health bureau,"Yang added, "We should break down the disease control work in detail and merge some departments into the health bureau, so that the health bureau is not only an administrative department, just like the Public Security Bureau has a lot of forensic technicians. "

Comprehensive examination

Although China has established a top-down four-level disease prevention and control network system from the national level to the county level, and established the world's largest and most extensive direct network reporting system for infectious diseases, it is still quite passive in the face of sudden outbreaks. In addition to the reasons mentioned above, there are also health emergency command and decision-making system operating less efficient factors.

Yang Gonghuan believes that public health emergency response, must be coordinated with all the support systems and forces, but from the new pneumonia epidemic at the beginning of the response, it is clearly problematic.

Reviewing the major public health emergencies in the past years, whether epidemic or natural disasters, we can find the deficiencies of the Health Emergency Command and decision-making system. In dealing with public health emergencies, China often only establishes a temporary command center for emergency response, and deploys personnel from relevant departments on a temporary basis. Due to the different working mechanism of each department, it is difficult to synchronize, which will lead to poor coordination and directly affect the efficiency of emergency decision-making and disposal. The new crown pneumonia epidemic at the beginning of the performance, but also once again highlights the construction of emergency command and decision-making system in different progress and uneven level.

In addition, other experts believe that insufficient investment in emergency funds, risk awareness is not strong enough, but also an important reason for the lack of emergency capacity. The United States Public Health Service is considered to be a public welfare undertaking provided by the government to all residents, and plays an important role in the prevention and control of various diseases. To some extent, the adequacy of government investment in public health emergency funds affects the establishment and improvement of health emergency management mechanism, and also plays a key role in promoting the equalization of basic health services.

Statistics show that China's total public health expenditure increased year by year from 2010 to 2016, but its proportion in total health expenditure remained almost unchanged, at the same time, the unreasonable input structure of some provinces is quoted from the paper "current situation and challenges of Health Emergency Management in China" , author Qu Teng, et Al. , August 2019.

The lack of government investment in public health is bound to affect infectious disease monitoring and early warning, emergency drills, publicity and education, emergency supplies reserves and other work. This is particularly true in less developed regions where fiscal security is lacking.

The new case of pneumonia, which is rare in the world, is not only a major test of scientific and economic strength, but also a major test of the country's governance. Hopefully, we will be able to take the exam seriously and get good results, from individuals to organizations and institutions, from the CDC system to other government departments.
